      <div class="docs-eyebrow">Documentation</div>
      <h1 class="docs-title">Data &amp; Privacy Policy</h1>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">1. Our Philosophy: Privacy by Design</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        Cuento is built on a Zero-PII (Personally Identifiable Information) model. We believe
        you should be able to tell stories without leaving a digital footprint.
      </p>
      <ul class="docs-list">
        <li><strong>No Emails:</strong> We do not collect or store email addresses.</li>
        <li><strong>No Real Data:</strong> Your account is identified solely by a nickname.</li>
        <li><strong>No Tracking:</strong> We do not use tracking cookies or sell user data.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">2. Public Content &amp; Narrative Integrity</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        This is a collaborative storytelling environment. To maintain the integrity and
        readability of the world for all players, in-game content — your roleplay posts,
        character sheets, and wanted character entries — is considered part of the shared
        narrative. By registering on any Cuento site, you grant the platform a perpetual
        license to retain and display this content to ensure story continuity, even after
        you leave the site. Upon account archival, this content is anonymised: your username
        is replaced by a generic identifier (e.g., <code>The_Nameless_One</code>).
      </p>
      <p class="docs-p">
        <strong>The Severance:</strong> Upon archival of your user account, we permanently
        destroy the technical link between your login credentials and your content. Once this
        link is severed, the action is irreversible — we cannot re-link posts to a new account
        because the connection no longer exists in our database.
      </p>
      <div class="callout">
        All non-game data — posts in general (out-of-character) topics, user settings, and
        similar personal content — is <strong>not</strong> anonymised and retained. It is
        deleted permanently when you use the Data Wipe Tool described in section 3.
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">3. Private Messages &amp; Full Data Erasure</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        Your private correspondence and personal data belong to you. We provide a unique
        mechanism for you to permanently erase all of it, even after you leave the platform.
      </p>
      <p class="docs-p">
        <strong>Recovery Codes:</strong> Upon registration, the system generates a set of
        unique recovery codes. Store these safely — they are your only cryptographic proof
        of ownership of your private data.
      </p>
      <p class="docs-p">
        <strong>Default Retention:</strong> If you archive your account, or if your account
        is banned, your DMs remain accessible to your conversation partners by default to
        preserve history. The link to your login credentials is severed, but the messages
        themselves are kept until you choose to wipe them.
      </p>
      <p class="docs-p">
        <strong>The Data Wipe Tool:</strong> Using your recovery code, you can trigger a
        permanent, irreversible deletion of all non-game data associated with your account —
        at any time, even without logging in, and without requiring approval from site
        administration or other participants. This includes:
      </p>
      <ul class="docs-list">
        <li>All private messages (DMs)</li>
        <li>Posts in general (out-of-character) topics</li>
        <li>User settings and account preferences</li>
        <li>Any other non-game personal data</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="docs-p">
        The following in-game content is <strong>not</strong> deleted — it is anonymised
        instead, to preserve narrative continuity for other players:
      </p>
      <ul class="docs-list">
        <li>In-character roleplay posts</li>
        <li>Character sheets</li>
        <li>Wanted character entries</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">4. User Responsibility &amp; Verification</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        Because we do not collect emails or real-world identity markers, we have no way to
        verify your identity via traditional support channels.
      </p>
      <div class="callout">
        If you lose both your password and your recovery codes, we cannot recover your private
        messages or delete your data for you. While administrators may be able to reset a
        password, doing so without the original keys will result in the permanent loss of all
        previous DMs.
      </div>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">5. Technical Security</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        Your DMs are protected using cryptographically safe private keys. Your password,
        recovery codes, private keys, and the content of your private messages are never
        stored in plain text.
      </p>
      <p class="docs-p">
        Neither the administrators nor the developers of the site can recover this information.
        This ensures that your private messages remain confidential between you and your
        intended interlocutor.
      </p>

      <h2 class="docs-h2">6. GDPR &amp; Regulatory Compliance</h2>
      <p class="docs-p">
        By removing the link between your login credentials and your content (anonymisation),
        Cuento ensures compliance with the core principles of the GDPR and CPPA regarding
        personal information protection.
      </p>
      <p class="docs-p">
        The Data Wipe Tool specifically fulfils your Right to Erasure, allowing you to
        permanently remove all non-game personal data even after your relationship with
        the platform has ended.
      </p>
